    <node id="PyMuPDF">
      <data key="d0">PyMuPDF</data>
      <data key="d1">parser</data>
      <data key="d2">PyMuPDF is an open-source Python library and tool primarily used for parsing and extracting text from PDF files. It also includes functionality for Optical Character Recognition (OCR), allowing it to read and convert images within the document into readable text. PyMuPDF handles various aspects of a PDF file, including reading headers, processing content extraction, and potentially manipulating or converting the document formats. The library is frequently used in applications involving NIST Cybersecurity Framework documents as exemplified by its use on files like "NIST.CSWP.29.pdf". It can be applied to parse and analyze different types of PDFs for extracting information pertinent to specific use cases, such as cybersecurity frameworks.</data>
