    <node id="NIST CSWP 29">
      <data key="d0">NIST CSWP 29</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">NIST CSWP 29 refers to specific documents and certifications related to cybersecurity, particularly within the context of the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) version 2.0. The document discusses aspects related to Certified Secure Wireless Professionals certification, a training program for cybersecurity professionals. It also references various components like roles, responsibilities, and authorities, as well as sections on recovery and privacy risk management in the framework.

The term "NIST CSWP 29" is associated with multiple certifications including NIST Cybersecurity Special Publication (CSWP), Certified Secure Web Programming (CSWP), and Certification for Security Whiplash Practitioners (CSWP). This document likely provides detailed guidelines, implementations examples, and structured approaches to cybersecurity practices. It also mentions specific sections within the framework like implementation examples and quick-start guides (QSGs), indicating a comprehensive approach towards cybersecurity standards and their practical application.

Furthermore, NIST CSWP 29 is related to various other NIST publications such as Cybersecurity Workforce Profile (CSWP) and Cybersecurity Special Publication (CSWP). It's mentioned that the document contains specific pages like page 14 for Informative References, page 20 for Recovery practices, and page 26 for specific frameworks. The reference also includes a section related to Privacy Risk Assessment Methodology (PRAM), highlighting its importance in cybersecurity.

Overall, NIST CSWP 29 is an integral part of the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 document, aligning with its context and providing structured guidelines for various roles and responsibilities within the framework.</data>
