    <node id="PyMuPDF Parser">
      <data key="d0">PyMuPDF Parser</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">PyMuPDF is a Python library primarily used for extracting text from PDF files, with applications in parsing and analyzing PDF documents. It has been utilized for various purposes including processing "NIST.CSWP.29.pdf" as well as the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 document. Additionally, it extracts metadata from PDF documents and aids in image-to-text conversion. The parser is also employed to process source files for information extraction directly from PDFs. While there are slight variations in how PyMuPDF is referred to or used across the provided descriptions—such as "extracting metadata," “used,” or specifying a particular document like "NIST.CSWP.29.pdf" or CSF 2.0—the core function of text extraction and parsing remains consistent.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3ae9e3476dacda5dbc0b092eee310a64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e234621b7f425933aeb1e42b348c4a32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b193a13851e6929cbb22da5ab360704&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cf0ecace48f517f2845c25e229bcaa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e0d0175165f5302cc1e6ae4c641c34d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6632abeaa757531b99f060efde3a5149&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4ee3b9aa47a173ae5b573628fc4788&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fc3ee5b64dc4bd0233d867af22d889a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2466c4a13bd6306d3a09498f94e8d834&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b0ca6812cf2474799c4e95a396ae1df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d6779a3859e0dd92a32b8ad4c053249&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c8948137c854edf2aec93f9cab81db1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b2ec81c9db8de5e80241030d36a77f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9e3ee337079a2ad4117c08435d5a020</data>
