    <node id="The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF)">
      <data key="d0">The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The NIST Cybersecurity Framework, also known as CSF, is a flexible framework for managing risks developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST). It refers to best practices that help organizations manage cybersecurity risks. The CSF version 2.0 introduces core functions: Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover. NIST Cybersecurity Framework describes these functions as guidelines for improving an organization's security posture. The framework covers the structure of cybersecurity management systems and is a conceptual model comprising five core functions. It emphasizes flexibility in application across all organizations regardless of size.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fd198cb863de8f31f9ae6a2d92b1914&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1006bc0fb3f33493a9bb69116ebeeb94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-827f48355d04a2a9eaac5548458d8e8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef0c2be3ac1a640a1e4f1a6297267b75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba7b2d86ee394df6f581db52e93726f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2a8cc9c75c9b5a3099bb67ae5079e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c6f7bae29996027737c7dc965ea0239&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55cf21cdfe6a7d01c11ae694b1df98ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-59ac33326a4521f610fc2ff4cbfef4a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e11f6b3f6a66a3301eb64bc576725e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b02aab9d01ec97358b87ff349bbe6c7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbd18a0ad44dbd415d46c115a340903d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25eb93c68ce1a37ae6e09b271db64dc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fa58a4b8ae6497e3096ccd2ed086335&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f30c6b17055366ece55bbe7e8a50f9d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ed7183dd79953837ed2e625c7bb3d7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fc3ee5b64dc4bd0233d867af22d889a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4dd323a57a5e201dbbabc38ad150d0a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8748963043426f14c1527712ec159b5e</data>
