    <node id="Cybersecurity Framework (CSF)">
      <data key="d0">Cybersecurity Framework (CSF)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cybersecurity Framework (CSF), also known as the NIST Cybersecurity Framework, is a structured approach developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology. It provides guidelines for managing cybersecurity risk within an organization, which includes various parts such as Core, Profiles and Tiers, and Online Resources. The CSF aims to offer a comprehensive strategy for identifying, protecting, responding, recovering, and improving the security posture of organizations across different organizational boundaries. As a framework by NIST, it offers guidance on managing cybersecurity risk effectively within an organization's operations, enhancing its resilience against cyber threats.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e6937a0dea6bdccfd0acd899789297fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4dd323a57a5e201dbbabc38ad150d0a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e02b7aa698b9c023dac6aead366390a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56f1498ba6ce64eefdb5e139e2a93c31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd8099546d6ba4f3178525229495d88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abdfb552a7b4b7f214088d47b88ea818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c34e6e4f53111e1e0df93b233b83242&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07520e3378ec637954e3df08cc822bf2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8748963043426f14c1527712ec159b5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51f93bf2d58b81a5311e2cb2ecaf430d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bdcf1715979a7e31cc08a2fbd03306f3</data>
