    <node id="PDF">
      <data key="d0">PDF</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">PDF refers to Portable Document Format, a common file format for documents often used in technical contexts like cybersecurity frameworks. The input text mentions NIST.CSWP.29.pdf as a specific PDF document type, which is stored and shared electronically. This document contains the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 information formatted in PDF format. It can be read by software such as PyMuPDF and enables easy viewing and sharing of its content, including detailed cybersecurity guidelines. The file extension indicates a PDF format for storing documents like the CSF 2.0 document.</data>
