    <edge source="NIST.CSWP.29.pdf" target="NIST Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)">
      <data key="d7">48.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The NIST Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF) is discussed in detail for its integration into existing cybersecurity frameworks such as CSF, with specific attention given to how it can be applied within a cybersecurity supply chain and as part of broader initiatives or strategies. The document also provides methodologies for risk assessment using the AI RMF within cybersecurity practices. Additionally, it offers instructions on applying the NIST AI RMF in conjunction with other existing frameworks like CSF 2.0 and C-SCRM. A case study illustrating how to apply the NIST AI RMF within the context of CSF 2.0 is included as well. Furthermore, the document details its use in a cybersecurity supply chain context and suggests its application within an overall cybersecurity strategy or framework like CSF 2.0.</data>
