    <edge source="The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0" target="Header">
      <data key="d7">28.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 is a comprehensive framework used for managing cybersecurity risk at an organization level. It contains various sections and headers that direct readers to different pages within the document.

Page 4 of the document references "List of Figures". Page 5 mentions the Preface of the NIST Cybersecurity Framework version 2.0, which indicates specific outcomes can be found on page 5. The header suggests detailed information is available on page 6 related to the framework and points out that a more specific location within the document, indicated by "NIST CSWP 29", is also referenced.

Page 7 of the document provides a reference for the Preface mention and indicates the content can be found in "source_file: NIST.CSWP.29.pdf". Page 8 confirms this through the header indicating this information is on page 8 within the file, under "The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0".

Reference to the framework on page 16 suggests a discussion related to cybersecurity risk management. The document mentions its title as "The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0" on Page 22.

Page 23 of the document references this content again, indicating that information about prioritization and threat environment is available on page 23. Further, it points out a specific reference to an organization located in Gaithersburg, MD, which can be found on page 29 within "NIST.CSWP.29.pdf".

The document contains various references and headers with details such as the version of NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) mentioned on February 26, 2024, and references to different locations and pages throughout the file. Each reference points readers to specific locations within "NIST.CSWP.29.pdf" for further information on cybersecurity risk management strategies and organizational location details.</data>
