    <edge source="NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0" target="Kind">
      <data key="d7">161.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The Kind property of the entity in the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 relates to its type, describing it as either an organizational process issue or simply part of a text document. The framework itself is identified as a text-based document with kind 'text', and this text includes descriptions that explain various aspects of managing cybersecurity risks through a textual format. Specifically, the document contains a textual explanation and a section labeled as a "text" which provides a comprehensive textual description of the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0's approach to risk management.</data>
      <data key="d9">document content,document type,document type specification,text,text extraction,text format,text kind,type of statement</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-86583643b07c1568b52f107766c93525&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0af2b2ff693fc69321fb689063551953&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bc458dd28316bb4e7070e39b19c5b38</data>
      <data key="d11">parsed_data/NIST.CSWP.29.md</data>
      <data key="d12">1773880318</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
