    <edge source="Cybersecurity Supply Chain Risk Management Practices for Systems and Organizations (SP 800-161r1)" target="NIST Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)">
      <data key="d7">17.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Cybersecurity Supply Chain Risk Management Practices for Systems and Organizations (SP 800-161r1) and NIST Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF) both discuss integrating AI RMF into existing cybersecurity practices. The document includes descriptions of how to apply, integrate, or use the NIST AI RMF within existing cybersecurity frameworks like C-SCRM. It also discusses discussions on integrating AI RMF with other enterprise risks and CSF for a comprehensive approach. One case study mentions applying AI RMF within the C-SCRM framework. The document suggests that AI RMF should be integrated into existing C-SCRM strategies, practices, and even combined with SP 800-161r1 cybersecurity supply chain risk management practices. Integration of AI RMF is highlighted as necessary for effective risk management. AI RMF is noted to be applicable in the context of SP 800-161r1's risk management process.</data>
